I use Nginx as a proxy in front of Next.js and this approach works to update the cache-control response header for static files

As a simple example, in the nginx `server` config:

```nginx
# Override Cache-Control for static image files, including those with optional query parameters
location ~* \.(jpg|jpeg|png|gif|ico|svg|webp)(\?.*)?$ {
    # Proxy through to Next.js
    proxy_pass http://localhost:3000;

    # Clear any existing Cache-Control header from Next.js
    proxy_hide_header Cache-Control;

    # Set new Cache-Control response header
    add_header Cache-Control "public, max-age=31536000, immutable" always;
}
```

