@timneutkens I had a similar issue having story files inside the pages directory and I tried ignoring them using the IgnorePlugin, but couldn't get it to work. Instead, what you can do is to add: `pageExtensions: ['page.tsx', 'page.ts', 'page.jsx', 'page.js']` to `next.config.js` and rename all of the files that **are pages**  to include `.page.tsx`

So if you have `home.tsx` and ´about.tsx´ you rename them to `home.page.tsx` and `about.page.tsx`

Read more in [the custom page extension config](https://nextjs.org/docs/api-reference/next.config.js/custom-page-extensions)

